<paragraph blockId="5.[151,986,965,992]" box="[151,986,965,992]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,986,965,992]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="5" pageNumber="129" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,986,965,992]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">
Key to the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Saussure" box="[413,545,965,992]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Calligaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[413,545,965,992]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Calligaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurring in the 
<collectingCountry box="[760,986,965,992]" name="Philippines" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Philippine Islands</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="129" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="129">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1035,1262]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="129">
1 Parapsidal furrows shallow, with few punctures. Anterior margin of scutellum with a shallow and irregular transverse furrow; scutellum dull with fine punctures (
<figureCitation box="[574,633,1064,1086]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[197,1390,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[197,1390,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3–8. 3–4, 7, Calligaster ilocana Selis, sp. nov. 5–6, 8, Calligaster williamsi Bequaert, 1940. 3, 5, Head of male in frontal view. 4, 6, Head of female in frontal view. 7–8, Mesoscutum and scutellum in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669324/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Male clypeus regularly convex, apical emargination semicircular and as wide as deep (
<figureCitation box="[284,343,1093,1115]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[197,1390,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[197,1390,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3–8. 3–4, 7, Calligaster ilocana Selis, sp. nov. 5–6, 8, Calligaster williamsi Bequaert, 1940. 3, 5, Head of male in frontal view. 4, 6, Head of female in frontal view. 7–8, Mesoscutum and scutellum in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669324/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Female clypeus more sparsely punctured on the disc (
<figureCitation box="[876,935,1093,1115]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[197,1390,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[197,1390,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3–8. 3–4, 7, Calligaster ilocana Selis, sp. nov. 5–6, 8, Calligaster williamsi Bequaert, 1940. 3, 5, Head of male in frontal view. 4, 6, Head of female in frontal view. 7–8, Mesoscutum and scutellum in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669324/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Head entirely black in both sexes............................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Bequaert" authorityName="Bequaert" authorityYear="1940" box="[1228,1437,1123,1144]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Calligaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="williamsi">
<emphasis box="[1228,1344,1123,1144]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">C. williamsi</emphasis>
Bequaert
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1035,1262]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="129">
- Parapsidal furrows defined and deep, densely punctured. Anterior margin of scutellum crenate, forming six deep pits; scutellum weakly shiny with big deep punctures and micropunctate interspaces (
<figureCitation box="[904,964,1181,1203]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[197,1390,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[197,1390,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3–8. 3–4, 7, Calligaster ilocana Selis, sp. nov. 5–6, 8, Calligaster williamsi Bequaert, 1940. 3, 5, Head of male in frontal view. 4, 6, Head of female in frontal view. 7–8, Mesoscutum and scutellum in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669324/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Male clypeus with a median transverse depression, apical emargination wider than deep (
<figureCitation box="[651,711,1211,1233]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[197,1390,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[197,1390,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3–8. 3–4, 7, Calligaster ilocana Selis, sp. nov. 5–6, 8, Calligaster williamsi Bequaert, 1940. 3, 5, Head of male in frontal view. 4, 6, Head of female in frontal view. 7–8, Mesoscutum and scutellum in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669324/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Female clypeus more densely punctured on the disc (
<figureCitation box="[1256,1317,1211,1233]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[197,1390,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[197,1390,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3–8. 3–4, 7, Calligaster ilocana Selis, sp. nov. 5–6, 8, Calligaster williamsi Bequaert, 1940. 3, 5, Head of male in frontal view. 4, 6, Head of female in frontal view. 7–8, Mesoscutum and scutellum in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669324/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Male with yellow lines on mandible and scape and rounded yellow spots above antennal insertions........ 
<taxonomicName authority="Selis" authorityName="Selis" authorityYear="2022" box="[1195,1350,1240,1262]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Calligaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ilocana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1195,1295,1240,1261]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">C. ilocana</emphasis>
Selis
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1360,1436,1240,1261]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1360,1436,1240,1261]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</subSubSection>
